76561198025087928,Recommended,427820,32727655,Posted: 24 June,all,UnOriginal_Bastard,"You know how there is occasionally a spinoff TV show that somehow takes the source material, does something completely different with it and just creates something cool in it's own right? This is kind of like that.Baldy is in fine form. This game is a gem which has spawned a few more in the series (Lara Croft GO, Dues Ex GO). While there's no doubt this game was designed for tablets and appears to be a casual puzzle game, the port to PC works brilliantly and the difficulty is pretty much perfect as it ramps up from basic to challenging.The minimalist art style is fresh and different, sounds and music are solid and the gameplay shines as you slowly accumulate new enemies, movement options, weapons and other diversion objects etc. The game drip feeds all these pieces into the game at a consistant pace so you never feel overwhelmed. While later levels are tricky, they never feel impossible and all the information you require is pretty much on the one screen. If you really get stuck there is a hint button to basically show you the solution.The game plays out similar to a board game. You just need to get baldy to the exit square. You move your piece 1 dot and the enemies also move 1 dot. Some patrol, some just guard certain points. You'll get access to certain equpiment etc to help get you past a level or you just need to time your movements correctly. A fair amount of the levels have multiple solutions, however in general you'll notice the level layout will give you a fair idea of what is required to solve the puzzle.There is plenty of content. You'll get 8+ hours playtime if you want to complete the game 100% (with all achievements). I didn't experience any technical issues. All achievements popped. If it's on special it's defintely worth picking up."
