,Recommended,427820,31985160,Posted: 26 May,all,DonRade,"I was hesitant at first to pick up a mobile port but with game being so cheap on sale I decided to try it out, and I’m glad I did. If you like puzzle games then you’ll like Hitman GO. The game is all about moving your figure around on a grid like levels trying to take out your targets. When you move, everybody else moves. Enemies have different abilities, there are pick up weapons, decoys, disguises, there are also escalators, manhole teleporters, locked doors and keys all working together to give your brain a challenge to figure out. What is also nice is that there is more than one way to finish a level. Some levels will require multiple plays to achieve 3 star rating, so there is some replayability. Overall the game can be finished and 100%ed in 7-8 hours.But one huge gripe I have with this game is its control scheme. Swiping makes sense on mobile, but not with a mouse. If your only available movement is up, down, left or right you could have used, oh I don’t know, freaking ARROWS? Or even just clicking on a spot would have made more sense than swiping. It would have been nice to at least have that option."
