76561198030786592,Recommended,427820,22228934,"Posted: 3 April, 2016",all,Andrew Ryan,"So much love for this game. Minimalistic, stylish and beautiful. Does a /surprisingly/ good job of capturing that 'essence' of Hitman games: outwitting, outmanuevering, and outgunning (sometimes) your foes. The pieces feel like chess: there isn't much ""variety"" in the pieces, but they are used with tremendous skill to build puzzles that never feel samey. One of the few games I've ever felt motivated to 100%, with special seals for each level (for beating it in X # of turns, or for beating it without killing anyone, etc.) Some of these were real headscratchers, but despite not being much of a puzzle game player, I never felt the urge to consult a walkthrough. Eventually, through experimentation, you will figure out solutions.The art is fantastic. Each level feels like a little artpiece, with figures captured in a variety of poses: people half-spilling coffee, or baggage handlers frozen mid-bag toss. This is really immersive, making you feel like the Hitman: walking consciously and coldly through a world of 'little idiots' unaware and naive to your presence. Just as though the world has stopped moving, while the Hitman stalks his prey. Very cool, and my favourite puzzle game to date.If it matters: 10/10"
,Recommended,427820,28967514,Posted: 2 January,all,Max2030,"This is a really fun casual puzzle game. I never knew turn based puzzle games existed before this, but here it is, and it's quite enjoyable. The goal in each level is simple: to go from point A to point B, which sounds quite boring. But it's how you get there is what makes the game interesting. If your enemy sees you, they will kill you.I like it so much that I also have it on my phone. That's where I got it first because it's a lot cheaper. If you like puzzles and you don't want to pay the full price, I recommend at least try it on the phone since it's inexpensive. I waited for it to go on sale and that's when I bought it on steam. I love its table top board game style. I find its neat and clean design aesthetically appealing.It's worth mentioning that there are three turn based 'Go' puzzle games by Square Enix: Hitman Go, Lara Croft Go, and Deus Ex Go. The mechanics in all three games are similar but the puzzles are quite different. The initial levels are there just to make you familiarize with the game mechanics and that's why they feel very similar at first. But as you progress, you will realize that the puzzles are quite different. I own all three on my Android phone and I love them all. Lara Croft Go has only been recently introduced to PC. Deus Ex: Go hasn't been out on PC yet. Hopefully it will."
