76561198102771498,Recommended,427820,21605041,"Posted: 3 March, 2016",all,Sonic and Hooters Forces,"FACT: 99% of all mobile games exist just to drain your wallet. I have found only three exceptions to this on my phone travels. A FMV game called ""Tender Loving Care"". A point and click game called ""Yesterday"". And this game, HITMAN GO.Hitman GO is a minimalist puzzle game take on the complex hitman series.  It prides itself on boiling down all the complexness of bloodmoney into a simple yet challenging puzzle game (Which is better then it sounds trust me) Enough talk lets assasinate some ♥♥♥♥♥es and dive right in to HITMAN GO!STORYWhile the other Hitman Games had a rich story as the cherry on top of tight gameplay, HITMAN GO has no story and doesnt really need one. Your a hitman. Kill your way to the exit of each level. Sometimes the level exit is replaced with a random guy you need to kill. No Big Deal.PRESENTATIONThe graphics arent HYPEREALISTIC 1020P HD However. The minamalist board game style is not only really nice and easy on the eyes but also isnt distracting when you are trying to play. Even though the layout is simple you still feel like your sneaking around a airport or a suburban apartment complex. The game is usualy silent to help you concintrate, but the smoothe sounds of Ave Maria kick in in the levels where you kill your target. Which usualy calms you down from rage quitting.GAMEPLAYThere are currently 5 chapters with two half chapters inspired by some of the other Hitman Games. All in All 91 levels with scaling difficulty. When you start out, its very simple. Get to the end of the level, dont get caught, attack gaurds from behind. But more and more gameplay elements get thrown in as you proceed such as everything from guns to gaurds with dogs and tazers. Mixing all these elements in with old things you learn is great at keeping you on your toes and makes for a great puzzle experience. There are also two alternate objectives for each level which requires you to finish the level whilst also doing something, like picking up a breifcase or killing everyone. Making a bit of replay-ability.FREEMIUM ASPECTSIn the mobile version  the only micro transactions were to pay for walkthroughs or ""hints"" if you got stuck on a level. This was great because it encouraged the player to get better and find the solution themselves. In the steam version, there are no micro transactions at all, so cheat to your hearts content! WARNING IF YOU USE THE INGAME HINTS YOU WILL NOT GET A ACHIEVMENT!Ranking: FULL PRICE BUY"
,Recommended,427820,23887949,"Posted: 28 June, 2016",all,Orion1189,"This was my third time buying Hitman GO, and it still impressed me. Enough to 100% it again. An excellently crafted puzzle game that does a surprisingly great job of also capturing many of the core elements of the Hitman games. And that's on top of the beautiful boardgame/diorama esthetic that is perfect throughout. The levels do a great job of providing a steady but fair difficulty curve, with the later levels in each box, and even more so the final levels of the game, providing a very hearty challenge, with the goal of completing all the optional objectives being especially mind-bending at times. There are a few levels or objectives that can feel a bit like duds when compared to the vast majority of the levels in the game that are great, and the camera/controls can be a bit of a pain in some levels (even with the alternate camera angles). It is also worth noting that I played entirely with a controller, and the game controls very well with one.All in all, Hitman GO is a puzzle game that has very simple mechanics at its core, with many layers of complexity steadily piled on throughout to keep those core mechanics feeling fun, with all that wrapped up in an awesome aesthetic. And that's exactly what I want from a great puzzle game. I'm looking forward to one day being able to buy Lara Croft GO again on Steam, as well as Deus Ex GO."
