,Recommended,427820,21425519,"Posted: 24 February, 2016",all,White,"Hitman GO beautifully encapsulates the Hitman experience all whilst switching the genre to a turn-based strategy game. Previously on mobile, with fantastic art style, ambient music and absolutely lovely environments inspired by physical board games and dioramas that look even better in higher resolutions, GO is still a game I adore.It uses all classic Hitman gameplay mechanics, such as disguises, timing your movement, learning enemy pathings, hiding in plain sight (here with help of a plant), sniper rifles and of course, 47's trusted Silverballers and mixes them up to create an enthralling little title that's both easy to get the hang of and difficult to master. Hey, it's just like the regular Hitman games!GO starts easy and slowly introduces more gameplay mechanics to the mix, ramping up the difficulty. The game is never too easy or too hard and even though I finished it multiple times on my Android device, I still have trouble with some challenges.Unfortunatelly, the only problem I had with this game is still present in this version - the challenges are uninspired, usually consisting of picking up the briefcase or finishing the board in a set amount of turns. In most cases, those challenges also cancel each other out (in most cases, you cannot waste turns on the briefcase when you're trying to finish the level fast) therefore, for hitting that 100%, you will have to finish the levels multiple times.The boards are never as long for it to become a hassle though and coming up with different strategies for different challenges starts feeling desirable as the game piles up its mechanics.I never found it frustrating or cheap, the difficulty curve is perfect and I would totally recommend this game for everybody. Not just Hitman fans, but also puzzle game enthusiasts."
